      • getRunLocation

        String getRunLocation()
        Gets the server to run on. This value will be one of:
        • A server name when one is specified
        • A user name when set to "Local"
        • "*" when set to run on any server
        • "" when set to prompt for a server name when enabled
        Returns:
        configured server run location

      • getIntervalType

        AgentInterval getIntervalType()
        Interval type for the agent
        Returns:
        the agent's interval type, or AgentInterval#NONE if not applicable

      • getInterval

        OptionalInt getInterval()
        Retrieves the interval value for the agent. The meaning of this number depends on the value of getIntervalType():
        NONE
        An empty value
        MINUTES
        The interval between invocations in minutes
        DAYS
        The interval between invocations in days*
        WEEK
        The interval between invocations in weeks*
        MONTH
        The interval between invocations in months*
        AgentInterval.EVENT
        An empty value

        Note: other than for MINUTES, the interval value is not expressible in Domino Designer and may not affect the behavior of the agent on the server.

        Returns:
        an OptionalInt describing the interval, or an empty one if it is not applicable

      • getRunLocalTime

        Optional<LocalTime> getRunLocalTime()
        Retrieves the local time of day when the agent should be run or start execution, if the interval type is not NONE or EVENT.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the local time to run, or an empty one if this value does not apply

      • getRunEndLocalTime

        Optional<LocalTime> getRunEndLocalTime()
        Retrieves the local time of day when the agent should no longer be executed. This only applies when the interval type is MINUTES.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the local end time of execution, or an empty one if the agent interval is not MINUTES

      • getRunDayOfWeek

        Optional<DayOfWeek> getRunDayOfWeek()
        Retrieves the day of the week that the agent should run. This only applies when the interval type is WEEK.
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the day of the week to execute, or an empty one if the agent interval is not WEEK

      • getRunDayOfMonth

        OptionalInt getRunDayOfMonth()
        Retrieves the 1-based day of the month that the agent should run. This only applies when the interval type is MONTH.
        Returns:
        an OptionalInt describing the day of the month to execute, or an empty one if the agent interval is not MONTH

      • isRunOnWeekends

        boolean isRunOnWeekends()
        Whether or not the agent runs on weekends, only relevant for DAILY or MORE_THAN_DAILY
        Returns:
        whether it runs on weekends. WEEKLY or MONTHLY returns true

      • getRunLog

        String getRunLog()

        Returns:
        String containing run log

      • getLastRunDuration

        OptionalLong getLastRunDuration()
        Analyses the last run log to work out the number of seconds for last run duration
        Returns:
        an OptionalLong describing the number of seconds between start and end of last run time, or an empty one if it has no run record

      • isLastRunExceededTimeLimit

        boolean isLastRunExceededTimeLimit()
        Analyses the last run log to work out if the last run exceeded the max run time for agents. Combine with getLastRunDuration() to work out what that max run time setting is.
        Returns:
        whether the last run time exceeded max run time for agents. If there is no run log, this will also be false
